Effective Date: [2024-09-01]
Introduction
Welcome to Device Tree! We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring that your personal information is handled securely and responsibly. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.
Information We Collect
1. Storage Browser and Manager
We access and manage your storage to help you browse and manage your files efficiently. This includes reading, writing, and organizing files on your device.
2. Device Information
We collect information about your device's RAM, battery status, CPU usage, installed apps, device specifications, display details, and network status to provide optimal performance and management insights.
3. System Information
We perform various tests and collect system data to ensure your device runs smoothly. This includes system diagnostics and performance monitoring.
How We Use Your Information
1. Local Processing: All the information we collect is used locally on your device. We do not upload any of your data to our servers or any third parties.
2. Performance Optimization: The collected data helps us optimize the performance of your device and enhance your user experience.
3. File Management: We use storage data to provide efficient file browsing and management functionalities.
Permissions We Require
To provide the above functionalities, Device Tree requires the following permissions:
MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE: To manage and organize files on your device.
Data Security
We take data security seriously and implement industry-standard measures to protect your information. All data processing is performed locally on your device, ensuring your personal data remains secure.
Your Rights
1. Access and Control: You have the right to access and control your device information. You can revoke permissions at any time through your device settings.
2. Data Deletion: You can request the deletion of your data by uninstalling the app.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated effective date. Please review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your data.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at
narayanverma008@gmail.com.
Thank you for trusting Device Tree with your device management needs!
